panels.content:
# Classification.* over time

The following graph shows the 3 classification.* fields over time: 

  * "classification.taxonomy", 
  * "classification.type", 
  * "classification.identifier". 

Select the taxonomy on top to filter and drill down to "type" and "identifier"
panels.title: Panel Title

targets.rawSql:
SELECT
  $__timeGroupAlias(date,$__interval),
  sum("count") as x,
  "classification.taxonomy"
FROM agg_ndim_day_all_tags
WHERE
  $__timeFilter(date) AND
  "classification.taxonomy" in ( $taxonomy) and 
  "source.asn" in ( $asn )
GROUP BY 1, 3
-- HAVING max("count") > 500
ORDER BY 1,3

SELECT
  $__timeGroupAlias(date,$__interval),
  sum("count") as x,
  "classification.type"
FROM agg_ndim_day_all_tags
WHERE
  $__timeFilter(date) AND
  "classification.taxonomy" in ( $taxonomy)  AND
  "classification.type" != 'some random string LTHADGDHTGTGYjhgsytsath'  and   -- grafana workaround
  "source.asn" in ( $asn )
GROUP BY 1, 3
-- HAVING max("count") > 500
ORDER BY 1,3

SELECT
  $__timeGroupAlias(date,$__interval),
  sum("count") as x,
  "classification.identifier"
FROM agg_ndim_day_all_tags
WHERE
  $__timeFilter(date) AND
  "classification.taxonomy" in ( $taxonomy)  AND
  "classification.identifier" != 'some random string LTHADGDHTGTGYjhgsytsath'  and   -- grafana workaround
  "source.asn" in ( $asn )
GROUP BY 1, 3
-- HAVING max("count") > 500
ORDER BY 1,3

panels.content:
# Top 10 protocols over time

The following graph shows the top 10 "protocol.application"s over time. Select the taxonomy on top to filter.
panels.title: Panel Title

targets.rawSql:
SELECT
  $__timeGroupAlias(date,$__interval),
  sum("count") as x,
  "protocol.application"
FROM agg_ndim_day_all_tags
WHERE
  $__timeFilter(date) AND
  "classification.taxonomy" in ( $taxonomy)  AND
  "classification.taxonomy" != 'some random string LTHADGDHTGTGYjhgsytsath' and   -- grafana workaround
  "protocol.application" != 'some random string ajhksjgklasjhga'  and  -- grafana workaround 
  "source.asn" in ( $asn )
GROUP BY 1, "protocol.application"
-- HAVING max("count") > 500
ORDER BY 1,3

panels.content:
# Data feeds over time

The following graphs shows the all "feed.name" and "feed.provider" over time. Select the taxonomy on top to filter.
Feed.provider shows which data feed gives us how much data (rows).
panels.title: Panel Title

targets.rawSql:
SELECT
  $__timeGroupAlias(date,$__interval),
  sum("count") as x,
  "feed.name"
FROM agg_ndim_day_all_tags
WHERE
  $__timeFilter(date) AND
  "classification.taxonomy" in ( $taxonomy)  AND
  "protocol.application" in ('https', 'rdp', 'tftp', 'cwmp', 'telnet', 'ntp', 'dns', 'ssdp', 'netbios-name', 'snmp') AND
  "classification.taxonomy" != 'some random string LTHADGDHTGTGYjhgsytsath'  and  -- grafana workaround
  "source.asn" in ( $asn )
GROUP BY 1, "feed.name"
-- HAVING max("count") > 500
ORDER BY 1,3

SELECT
  $__timeGroupAlias(date,$__interval),
  sum("count") as x,
  "feed.provider"
FROM agg_ndim_day_all_tags
WHERE
  $__timeFilter(date) AND
  "classification.taxonomy" in ( $taxonomy)  AND
  -- "protocol.application" in ('https', 'rdp', 'tftp', 'cwmp', 'telnet', 'ntp', 'dns', 'ssdp', 'netbios-name', 'snmp') AND
  "classification.taxonomy" != 'some random string LTHADGDHTGTGYjhgsytsath'   and -- grafana workaround
  "source.asn" in ( $asn )
GROUP BY 1, "feed.provider"
-- HAVING max("count") > 500
ORDER BY 1,3

panels.content:
# Malware over time

The following graphs shows the all "malware.name" stats over time. Please note that this only makes sense for the taxonomy 'malicious code'.
panels.title: Panel Title

targets.rawSql:
SELECT
  $__timeGroupAlias(date,$__interval),
  sum("count") as x,
  "malware.name"
FROM agg_ndim_day_all_tags
WHERE
  $__timeFilter(date) AND
  "classification.taxonomy" = 'malicious code' AND
  "classification.taxonomy" != 'some random string LTHADGDHTGTGYjhgsytsath' and    -- grafana workaround
  "malware.name" != 'some random string LTHADGDHTGTGYjhgsytsath' AND
  "source.asn" in ( $asn )
GROUP BY 1, "malware.name"
-- HAVING max("count") > 500
ORDER BY 1,3

panels.description: This lists the number of distinct IP addresses we see for each country over time. Of course, a focus is on Austria. So the stats are pretty clearly dominated by "AT". But we also (by accident) get data from other countries. Sometimes, "AT" and "AU" (Australia) get confused.

targets.rawSql:
SELECT
  $__timeGroupAlias(date,$__interval),

FROM agg_ndim_day_all_tags
WHERE
  $__timeFilter(date) AND
  "classification.taxonomy" in ( $taxonomy ) AND
  "classification.taxonomy" != 'some random string LTHADGDHTGTGYjhgsytsath' and    -- grafana workaround
  "source.geolocation.cc" != 'some random string LTHADGDHTGTGYjhgsytsath'
GROUP BY 1, 3
-- HAVING max("count") > 500
ORDER BY 1,3
